{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be88-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"18236"},"text":"§ 18236.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contributions to States; other use permitted by States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be89-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Contributions under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s18233"},"text":"section 18233 of this title","children":[],"tail":" are subject to such terms as the Secretary of Defense, after consulting the Committee on Armed Services of the Senate and the Committee on Armed Services of the House of Representatives, considers necessary for the purposes of this chapter. Except as otherwise agreed when the contribution is made, a facility provided by a contribution under paragraph (3) or (4) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s18233/a"},"text":"section 18233(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" may be used jointly by units of two or more reserve components of the armed forces only to the extent that the State considers practicable."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A contribution made for an armory or readiness center under paragraph (4) or (5) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s18233/a"},"text":"section 18233(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" may not exceed the sum of—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 100 percent of the cost of architectural, engineering and design services (including advance architectural, engineering and design services under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s18233/e"},"text":"section 18233(e) of this title","children":[],"tail":"); and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a percentage of the cost of construction (exclusive of the cost of architectural, engineering and design services) calculated so that upon completion of construction the total contribution (including the contribution for architectural, engineering and design services) equals 75 percent of the total cost of construction (including the cost of architectural, engineering and design services).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of computing the cost of construction under this subsection, the amount contributed by a State may not include the cost or market value of any real property that it has contributed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" If a State acquires, constructs, expands, rehabilitates, or converts a facility with amounts contributed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s18233"},"text":"section 18233 of this title","children":[],"tail":", it may—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" permit persons or organizations other than members and units of the armed forces to use the facility under such leases or other agreements as it considers appropriate; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be8f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" apply amounts received under those leases or agreements to the cost of maintaining the facility.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be90-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Except as otherwise agreed when the contribution is made, and except as the agreement is later changed, a State may not permit any use or disposition of the facility that would interfere with its use—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be91-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" for administering and training the reserve components of the armed forces; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be92-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s18236/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in time of war or national emergency, by other units of the armed forces or by the United States for any other purpose.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idabc5be93-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/122"},"text":"70A Stat. 122","children":[],"tail":", § 2236; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/40"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(40)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1456"},"text":"72 Stat. 1456","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/214/s3/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–214, § 3(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), (e)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/170"},"text":"96 Stat. 170","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/167/tVII/s702/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–167, title VII, § 702(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/985"},"text":"99 Stat. 985","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661/dA/tXIII/s1343/a/11"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661, div. A, title XIII, § 1343(a)(11)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3993"},"text":"100 Stat. 3993","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 18236 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1664/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1664(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (8), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3010"},"text":"108 Stat. 3010","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/dA/tXV"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, div. A, title XV","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1501(b)(36), 1502(a)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/498"},"text":"110 Stat. 498","children":[],"tail":", 502; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/dA/tX/s1067/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65, div. A, title X, § 1067(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/774"},"text":"113 Stat. 774","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dB/tXXVIII/s2807/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [div. B, title XXVIII, § 2807(b)(2)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–415.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idabc5be94-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idabc5be95-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idabc5be96-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"1956 ","children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(d) (1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(d) (less 1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-11/ch945/s4/d"},"text":"Sept. 11, 1950, ch. 945, § 4(d)","children":[],"tail":", (e), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/830"},"text":"64 Stat. 830","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(e) (less last 87 words).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(d)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(e) (last 87 words).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Appropriate references to the Territories, Puerto Rico, and the District of Columbia are inserted throughout the revised section to reflect 50:886(b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “and conditions” are omitted as covered by the word “terms”. The words “considers necessary for” are substituted for the words “shall deem necessary to accomplish”. The words “used jointly by units of two or more reserve components of the armed forces” are substituted for the words “joint utilization”, to reflect 50:886(d).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “the construction to which it is to be applied” are substituted for the words “the additional or improved facilities to be constructed”, since, under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2233"},"text":"section 2233 of this title","children":[],"tail":", contributions may be made for other purposes as well as additions and improvements. The words “may not include” are substituted for the words “shall be exclusive of”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c)(1), the words “from time to time” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c)(2), the words “defray in whole or in part” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words “except as the agreement is later changed” are substituted for the words “by subsequent modifications of the agreement.” The words “units of” and “at no time” are omitted as surplusage. The words “United States” are substituted for the words “Federal Government”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idabc5be97-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idabc5be98-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"1958 ","children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2236(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(d) (1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"50:883(d) (less 1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-09/ch662/s1/e"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1955, ch. 662, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/593"},"text":"69 Stat. 593","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “may be used jointly” are substituted for the words “shall be subject to joint utilization”. The words “and conditions” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idabc5be99-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idabc5be9a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or readiness center” after “armory” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65","children":[],"tail":" substituted “and the Committee on Armed Services” for “and the Committee on National Security”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/s1502/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, § 1502(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Committee on Armed Services of the Senate and the Committee on National Security of the House of Representatives” for “Committees on Armed Services of the Senate and the House of Representatives”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/s1501/b/36"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, § 1501(b)(36)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “18233(e)” for “2233(e)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1664/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1664(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2236"},"text":"section 2236 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1664/b/8/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1664(b)(8)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “18233” for “2233” and “paragraph (3) or (4) of section 18233(a)” for “section 2233(a)(3) or (4)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1664/b/8/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1664(b)(8)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paragraph (4) or (5) of section 18233(a)” for “clause (4) or (5) of section 2233(a)” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1664/b/8/B/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1664(b)(8)(B)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of par. (2) by substituting “section 18233(e)” for “section 2233(e)”, could not be executed because the words “section 2233(e)” did not appear in par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1664/b/8/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 1664(b)(8)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “18233” for “2233” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, territory, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, or the District of Columbia, as the case may be,” after “contributed by a State” in last sentence."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–167","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (b) read as follows: “A contribution made for an armory under section 2233(a